page.title: 16Woolley Feast
page.content: Woolley Feast is held evey year on the Saturday nearest to St.Peter's Day. On 29th June,1985 celebrations began at 1.30 p.m. with a decorated bicycle competition. Races began at 2 o'clock for all children with a Donkey Derby novelty race for families.I like the obstacle race best.After the Donkey Derby everyone could have free ice cream.Cups were presented to the winning boy and girl.Anna and I came first,We share the cup for one year each.Afterwards we all had tea. The Disco started at 7.30p.m.I was first there and I requested Frankie goes to Hollywood,but it wasn't played till the end.The DJ put on the Conga. I was leader and led them out of the school and round it.
